# NiteOS Cloud Production Environment — NiteOS VPS (31.97.126.86)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to infra/cloud.env on the NiteOS VPS and fill in ALL values.
# NEVER commit infra/cloud.env — it is gitignored.
# Generate passwords: openssl rand -base64 32
#
# Deployment: docker compose -f infra/docker-compose.cloud.yml --env-file infra/cloud.env up -d
# See: docs/DEPLOY_NITEOS_VPS.md for the full deployment runbook.

# ── Domains ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DOMAIN=peoplewelike.club
ACME_EMAIL=admin@peoplewelike.club

# ── Traefik port offset ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The NiteOS VPS uses nginx (host) as the ingress on :80/:443, routing to
# Traefik in Docker via upstream proxy_pass. Traefik does NOT need to bind
# :80/:443 directly — nginx handles public ingress.
#
# If running Traefik directly on :80/:443 (no nginx layer):
#   TRAEFIK_PORT_SUFFIX=   (empty — standard ports)
# If running Traefik on offset ports behind nginx:
#   TRAEFIK_PORT_SUFFIX=:8443
#
# Current NiteOS VPS setup: nginx → Traefik. Use empty unless changing ingress.
TRAEFIK_PORT_SUFFIX=

# ── Cloudflare DNS-01 TLS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Traefik uses Cloudflare DNS-01 challenge for Let's Encrypt (required for Cloudflare-proxied domains).
# Create API token at: https://dash.cloudflare.com/profile/api-tokens
# Required permissions: Zone > DNS > Edit, Zone > Zone > Read
CF_DNS_API_TOKEN=REPLACE_WITH_CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN

# ── Traefik dashboard (htpasswd format, generate with: htpasswd -nB admin) ───
TRAEFIK_DASHBOARD_USERS=admin:$$2y$$10$$REPLACE_WITH_HTPASSWD_HASH

# ── Postgres ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Used by postgres service init AND as part of DATABASE_URL for all services.
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=CHANGEME_use_openssl_rand_base64_32

# ── Redis ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_PASSWORD=CHANGEME_use_openssl_rand_base64_32

# ── Auth service — JWT signing key ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Generate:
#   mkdir -p infra/secrets
#   openssl genrsa -out infra/secrets/jwt_private_key.pem 2048
#   openssl rsa -in infra/secrets/jwt_private_key.pem -pubout -out infra/secrets/jwt_public_key.pem
# The compose file mounts infra/secrets/jwt_private_key.pem as a bind volume.
# (Path used by auth service: JWT_PRIVATE_KEY_PATH=/run/secrets/jwt_private_key.pem)

# ── Payments — Stripe ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use live keys for production; test keys for staging.
STRIPE_API_KEY=sk_live_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_STRIPE_KEY
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_WEBHOOK_SECRET

# ── Admin console ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SESSION_SECRET must be at least 32 random characters.
SESSION_SECRET=CHANGEME_use_openssl_rand_base64_32

# ── Guest web ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Separate secret for guest session cookies (iron-session).
GUEST_SESSION_SECRET=CHANGEME_use_openssl_rand_base64_32
# Stripe publishable key (safe to expose client-side — used for checkout redirect).
STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_live_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# Radio stream URL — MP3/AAC stream served by stream.peoplewelike.club.
NEXT_PUBLIC_RADIO_STREAM_URL=https://stream.peoplewelike.club/stream
# Radio API base URL — AzuraCast now-playing endpoint is /api/nowplaying.
NEXT_PUBLIC_RADIO_API_URL=https://radio.peoplewelike.club

# ── Grafana ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GRAFANA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=CHANGEME_use_openssl_rand_base64_32

# ── NiteOS VPS deployment notes ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Target: 31.97.126.86 (Ubuntu 22.04 LTS, Docker 29.2.1, SSH hardened, 4 GB swap)
# Full runbook: docs/DEPLOY_NITEOS_VPS.md
#
# Quick steps:
# 1. Clone repo to /opt/niteos on the NiteOS VPS
# 2. Copy this file: cp infra/cloud.env.example infra/cloud.env && nano infra/cloud.env
# 3. Create secrets dir: mkdir -p infra/secrets && chmod 700 infra/secrets
# 4. Generate JWT keys (see Auth service section above)
# 5. Create acme.json: touch infra/traefik/acme.json && chmod 600 infra/traefik/acme.json
# 6. Run preflight: bash scripts/preflight-cloud.sh
# 7. Run migrations: bash scripts/migrate.sh  (requires DATABASE_URL or postgres container)
# 8. Start stack: make cloud-up
# 9. Verify: bash scripts/healthcheck-cloud.sh
# 10. Smoke test: NITECORE_PASSWORD=<pw> bash scripts/smoke-test-pilot.sh
#
# Access after deploy:
#   https://api.peoplewelike.club/healthz
#   https://admin.peoplewelike.club
#   https://grafana.peoplewelike.club
#   https://os.peoplewelike.club  (guest web)
